#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:9
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:11
msgid ""
"There is a requirement to expose the audio hardware that accelerates various "
"tasks for user space such as sample rate converters, compressed stream "
"decoders, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:15
msgid ""
"This is description for the API extension for the compress ALSA API which is "
"able to handle \"tasks\" that are not bound to real-time operations and "
"allows for the serialization of operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:20
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:22
msgid "The main requirements are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:24
msgid ""
"serialization of multiple tasks for user space to allow multiple operations "
"without user space intervention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:27
msgid "separate buffers (input + output) for each operation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:29
msgid "expose buffers using mmap to user space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:31
msgid "signal user space when the task is finished (standard poll mechanism)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:34
msgid "Design"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:36
msgid ""
"A new direction SND_COMPRESS_ACCEL is introduced to identify the passthrough "
"API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:39
msgid ""
"The API extension shares device enumeration and parameters handling from the "
"main compressed API. All other realtime streaming ioctls are deactivated and "
"a new set of task related ioctls are introduced. The standard read/write/"
"mmap I/O operations are not supported in the passthrough device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:44
msgid ""
"Device (\"stream\") state handling is reduced to OPEN/SETUP. All other "
"states are not available for the passthrough mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:47
msgid ""
"Data I/O mechanism is using standard dma-buf interface with all advantages "
"like mmap, standard I/O, buffer sharing etc. One buffer is used for the "
"input data and second (separate) buffer is used for the output data. Each "
"task have separate I/O buffers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:52
msgid ""
"For the buffering parameters, the fragments means a limit of allocated tasks "
"for given device. The fragment_size limits the input buffer size for the "
"given device. The output buffer size is determined by the driver (may be "
"different from the input buffer size)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:58
msgid "State Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:60
msgid "The passthrough audio stream state machine is described below::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:82
msgid "Passthrough operations (ioctls)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:84
msgid "All operations are protected using stream->device->lock (mutex)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:87
msgid "CREATE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:88
msgid ""
"Creates a set of input/output buffers. The input buffer size is "
"fragment_size. Allocates unique seqno."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:91
msgid ""
"The hardware drivers allocate internal 'struct dma_buf' for both input and "
"output buffers (using 'dma_buf_export()' function). The anonymous file "
"descriptors for those buffers are passed to user space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:96
msgid "FREE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:97
msgid ""
"Free a set of input/output buffers. If a task is active, the stop operation "
"is executed before. If seqno is zero, operation is executed for all tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:102
msgid "START"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:103
msgid ""
"Starts (queues) a task. There are two cases of the task start - right after "
"the task is created. In this case, origin_seqno must be zero. The second "
"case is for reusing of already finished task. The origin_seqno must identify "
"the task to be reused. In both cases, a new seqno value is allocated and "
"returned to user space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:109
msgid ""
"The prerequisite is that application filled input dma buffer with new source "
"data and set input_size to pass the real data size to the driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:112
msgid ""
"The order of data processing is preserved (first started job must be "
"finished at first)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:115
msgid ""
"If the multiple tasks require a state handling (e.g. resampling operation), "
"the user space may set SND_COMPRESS_TFLG_NEW_STREAM flag to mark the start "
"of the new stream data. It is useful to keep the allocated buffers for the "
"new operation rather using open/close mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:121
msgid "STOP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:122
msgid ""
"Stop (dequeues) a task. If seqno is zero, operation is executed for all "
"tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:126
msgid "STATUS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../sound/designs/compress-accel.rst:127
msgid ""
"Obtain the task status (active, finished). Also, the driver will set the "
"real output data size (valid area in the output buffer)."
msgstr ""

